Explanation of the Tests:
Test 1: test_calculate_altitude_valid_pressure tests that the altitude is correctly calculated for standard atmospheric pressure (1013.25 hPa).
Test 2: test_calculate_altitude_high_pressure tests that the function returns -1 when the pressure exceeds 1100 hPa (which is considered too high for valid altitude calculations).
Test 3: test_calculate_altitude_high_altitude tests that the function returns -2 when the calculated altitude exceeds 40,000 feet.
